        ],
        "evidence": [
          "File uses @app.route('/results/<uuid>/strings', ...) and @app.route('/results/<uuid>/strings/download', ...) with no import of 'app'.",
          "File calls sqlite3.connect(DB_PATH) with no import of 'DB_PATH'; both names were globals in the old CLI/build/lib/multivol/api.py monolith.",
          "grep -r 'api_strings_extension' finds zero references across the production codebase \u2014 the file is dead code from the pre-Blueprint migration."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Delete CLI/multivol/api_strings_extension.py. The strings routes are already handled in scan.py via the Blueprint pattern. If any strings endpoint is missing, add it to CLI/multivol/api_server/routes/scan.py using get_db_connection() and the existing Blueprint pattern.",
        "reasoning": "",
