          "memprocfs.py:29: 'active_sessions = {}' module-level dict is the sole source of truth for live container sessions; there is no DB-backed recovery \u2014 sessions are lost on restart with no cleanup of orphaned Docker containers.",
          "Neither dict is reachable from outside the route module (no service layer), so any other module that needs to query or modify session/task state must import these route modules, pulling in Flask/Docker dependencies."
